pr_body:
This pull request includes all the work for the GSoC project of including competing destination estimation into SpInt module.
For more information please visit my blog https://lenkahas.com/post/gsoc.html.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 680066313, 'comment_body': 'This should probably be removed from the final file.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 30, 16, 30, 27, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ljwolf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 680066787, 'comment_body': 'The timings & the printing can also be removed for the final submission', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 30, 16, 30, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ljwolf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 680069170, 'comment_body': "As we talked about on our call today, the final signature for this function should look like:

`def accessibility(origins, destinations, distances, weights, masses, all_destinations=False):`

where each input is the same length vector. You may want to check the types/shapes of the input to 
- [ ] make sure they're all `numpy.ndarray`s (and maybe `numpy.asarray` them if they're not)
- [ ] check that they're all the same length", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 30, 16, 32, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ljwolf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 680070922, 'comment_body': 'If you prefix this with a `_`, like `_generate_dummy_flows()`, then python will "hide" it from users and avoid showing it when people look at the module. 

You can see this, for example, in [esda/map_comparison.py](https://github.com/pysal/esda/blob/master/esda/map_comparison.py#L13) where the `_overlay` and `_cast` functions are used by the module, but we don't want the users to see them/use them directly. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 30, 16, 34, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ljwolf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 680071265, 'comment_body': "I wouldn't have `generate_dummy_flows` in the init! ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 30, 16, 34, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ljwolf', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 680072475, 'comment_body': "I don't think this does what you think it does! check what `flow['results_all=False']` looks like! 

You may want to use something like `numpy.testing.assert_allclose` or `numpy.testing.assert_array_equal`, which are designed to compare numpy arrays.
